annotation.TEXT: Ow, my tootsie pops!
There we go!
Okay, interesting things start happening again after I clear this room.

There we go! However, instead of saving and quitting to escape, I can just press "R" to suicide, which sends me back to the previous checkpoint. (Thanks go to UltraLeet31337 for informing me about this.)
Ow, my butt! Hmm... I guess I have to take control there, so it's not completely automatic.
Nope, no need to take the warp this time (though I can't reach it while that overhang is there anyway), since I've got everything now.
Ld, nb yizrm!
Yeah, maybe that was indeed the problem...
Huh. I wonder why this room on the map isn't filled in...
This room was easy for me last time, and I don't think that's changed.
Ah, yes. The Machine room, which I skipped due to a level design flaw/feature last time. This time, I'll play it for realsies!
Oh, yeah. That block. Also, you might turn down your volume a bit... right now!
Ow, the extreme corner of my hitbox!

Yep, "R" worked, although we've lost the music temporarily. I wonder why the teleporters seemed to glitch out like that? Is it due to how I entered that teleporter room while on the side edges of the screen?
Ow, my rear!
Ow, my leftmost toe! Well, that didn't work, but maybe I threw off the way the room worked due to my momentum as I first entered. I'll try resetting the room entirely and see if it works this time.
Alright, now supposedly, this room (and the next) work automatically...
...D'oh! Why did I do that? I knew very well where that warp took me! Sigh... (Click here to skip to the end of the automatic room again.)
Ah, yes. This automatic room. Oh, but I want to try hitting the lower teleporter down there, since the game will automatically send me to the upper one if I do nothing...
Ow, my caboose! Well, that didn't exactly work. Wasn't even close. I'd better take control when I get over there again.
Ha, now that I know there's horizontal wraparound down here in this room, it's easy!
Oh, I remember this branching path. And, since I've already done everything to the left and gotten the trinket over there, I'll just head down from here this time.
Argh. Once again, why am I struggling with this?
...Really? It sent me back here. Oookay... I guess I've gotta "play" this automatic room again. (Click here to skip to the end of it.)
Okay, this time, I warped correctly. There must've been an odd quirk in those warps that made them malfunction when I entered the room while on the side edges of the screen or something...
And, that's it! Awesome! I now have a ** showing next to A New Dimension, so I'm completely done with this level, finally!
Hello, and welcome to the finale of A New Dimension in VVVVVV!
Oh, I know why. When I redid this part of the level off screen after the events of part 5 ("13 Epsilon"), I didn't revisit that room. Well, I'll fix that now!

Anyway, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through A New Dimension! Next time, I might decide to try 333333 (Easy Mode) again, or maybe try something else first. I haven't decided yet. Whatever I decide, see you next time! To be continued...
Same as the other "It's a trap!" teleporter, except I end up on the left side of the upper room. Alright, let's move on.
Ow, my wedgie!
There's still a lot of open spaces on the map, but I'm going to assume they're "out-of-bounds" areas that have nothing in them.
Ow, my bottom! (Or maybe my top, from that perspective.)
Alright, made it that time!
Alright, I'm gonna go through some familiar territory without anything special happening for a while, so click here if you want to skip to the next interesting thing that happens.
There's one last look at my stats (looks like I've died 28 times in this episode), and I'll save the game too, for good measure.
Ow, my butt again!
Oh, remember how I got myself hopelessly stuck using that glitch in this room last time? Here, let me demonstrate it again, if I can.
As usual, here's a quick look at the map and my stats...
Yep, today, I'm finally gonna fully complete this level... I hope.
Umm... What the heck? Did something break?
Huh. Well, that time I didn't die to those spikes over here, even though it looked like I appeared to take the same path...
Okay, this time, let's go to the warp on the left like I'm supposed to!
Okay, seriously. Stop screwing up on this easy stuff.
Okay, there we go. Finally.

Alright, I'm going to go through some more familiar rooms without anything special happening, besides me dying multiple times in rooms that should be easy. Click here to skip to the next interesting thing not related to me dying.
This room's mostly automatic as well, except I have to take control near the end to avoid the teleporter that sends me backwards.
And, that teleporter just leads me up here. So, it's pointless. But, what about the teleporter in the nearly identical "It's a trap!" room after going left just once?
Let's try not being on the side edges of the screen as I enter that room this time...
I wonder if I was supposed to land on a moving platform here automatically, but Souleye didn't set them properly or something...
Ow, my private quarters!
And, that room is done, but does this room also work automatically?
Ow, my middle toes!
Oh, wow. It certainly is! And I bet the room above is also automatic!
That's really weird, though. Can I at least escape by pressing "R"?
Wait, is the Machine room another automatic room?
Okay, I'm nearing the end here...
I still wonder what "rollercoasting" means... Maybe it's referring to the automatic rooms?
And here's "THE END!" room again. You'll notice that I put this tiny overhang back, which I did after I made the video for part 6 ("13 Zeta"), because that's how the level originally was.
Come on, I didn't have this much trouble with this room last time...
There we go! That's probably how it's meant to be done, instead of trying to slip between the spikes where I got my butt poked a couple times.
Maybe eventually I'll land on a platform?
Maybe I'm trying too hard and overthinking it?
Those previous rooms being automatic would explain the "No more slacking!" title of this room, except for the fact that the last room didn't work correctly without the player taking control...
Well, I can still bring up the pause menu, and you can get a better look at this teleporter room as I'm bringing up and putting away the menu...
Whoops! I didn't mean to go left a second time yet, but I can still go back and check that teleporter.
Nope. Still easy. On the other hand, this harpsichord is not so easy...
Oh, come on! I totally had that!
Hmm... There doesn't seem to be any need to go all the way to the right in that upper room. Also, I haven't tried the teleporter in this room yet...
